# Transmission Simulation

This folder contains the input file(model_1.in,model_2.in,model_3.in,model_4.in,model_5.in) and Python script(Make_model of N transmission.ipynb and simulation of N transmission.ipynb ) used to perform sequential Cloudy transmission simulations.

## Contents

- `new_test.in` – Template Cloudy input file.
- `transmission.py` – Python script that generates and runs the transmission models.
- `model_*.in` – Cloudy input files generated for each transmission.
- `wr_trans*.trn` – Transmitted continuum files produced by each simulation.

## Description

The Python script generates `N` Cloudy input files (`model_1.in`, `model_2.in`, ..., `model_N.in`) from the template `new_test.in`.

For each transmission:

- The transmitted continuum (`wr_trans(n-1).trn`) from the previous model is used as the incident continuum for the next model.
- A new Cloudy input file (`model_n.in`) is generated.
- Running the input file produces a new transmitted continuum (`wr_transn.trn`), which serves as the input for the following transmission.

This process simulates the evolution of the radiation field as it propagates through successive shells.

## Visualization

The notebook includes plots of:

- The incident continuum for each transmission.
- The incident and net transmitted continua for comparison after each simulation.
- The incident and transmitted continua for comparison after each simulation.
